jQuery CSS classes manipulation
---------------------------------------------------
jQuery provides different methods like addClass(), removeClass(), toggleClass to manipulate css classes assigned to HTML elements.


addClass() adds one or more classes to the selected elements.

removeClass() removes classes from the selected elements.

toggleClass() add or removes one or more classes from the selected elements.

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
<title>remove demo</title>
<style>
.paracss
{
color:blue;
text-transform: uppercase;

}
.highlightpara
{
background-color: yellow;
}
</style>
<script type="text/javascript" src="https://code.jquery.com/jquery-3.7.1.min.js"></script>
<script>
$(document).ready(function(){
$(".btnempty").click(function(){
$(".mydiv").empty();
});
$(".btnremove").click(function(){
$("#p1").remove();
});
$(".btnhref").click(function(){
$("a").removeAttr("href");
});

$(".btncss").click(function(){
$("#p2").addClass("paracss highlightpara");

});

$(".btncssrem").click(function(){
$("#p2").removeClass("highlightpara");
});
$(".btncsstog").click(function(){
$("#p2").toggleClass("paracss");
});
});
</script>
</head>
<body>
<div class="mydiv">
<h1>Welcome</h1>
<p>Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet consectetur adipisicing elit. Blanditiis necessitatibus temporibus quas quibusdam ex odio, voluptates ratione similique animi error laboriosam officia, dolorem pariatur. Iusto voluptates ut veritatis ducimus nemo.</p>
<button type="button" class="btnempty">empty</button>
<button type="button" class="btnremove">Remove</button>
</div>
<p id="p1">Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet consectetur adipisicing elit. Blanditiis necessitatibus temporibus quas quibusdam ex odio, voluptates ratione similique animi error laboriosam officia, dolorem pariatur. Iusto voluptates ut veritatis ducimus nemo.</p>
<b>Bold</b>
<a href="https://www.google.com">Google</a>
<button type="button" class="btnhref">remove Attribute </button>

<p id="p2">This paragraph is used to implement css.</p>
<button type="button" class="btncss">Add CSS class</button>
<button type="button" class="btncssrem">Remove CSS class</button>
<button type="button" class="btncsstog">Toggle CSS class</button>

</body>
</html>
